repository-code: "https://github.com/gerasimos/knowledge-operations-kas"
abstract: >-
  Two AI systems can both be called "RAG" while performing fundamentally
  different kinds of knowledge work; conversely, two systems can use different
  substrates—vectors, SQL, graphs, or tools—while satisfying the same workload
  requirement. This mismatch makes architecture-centered labels a poor guide to
  capability. This paper proposes a capability model for knowledge-augmented AI
  systems based on the knowledge operations they perform reliably, rather than
  on the data formats, stores, or orchestration patterns they use. The model
  profiles systems by knowledge operations (retrieve, scope, interpret,
  combine, compute, traverse, plan-and-act, govern, evaluate), introducing
  seven operation archetypes (K0–K6), a governance scale (G0–G5), and an
  evaluation discipline applied across every operation. The result is a
  multi-dimensional capability profile rather than a single maturity level,
  supporting evaluation per workload rather than per industry, vendor stack,
  or architectural fashion.
